			<CASNumber>7550-45-0</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Titanium tetrachloride, also known as titanium(IV) chloride or TiCl4, is a colorless volatile liquid that hydrolyzes in air with the emission of white clouds. It is used in the Kroll process for converting titanium ores into titanium metal. Despite titanium being the fourth most-abundant metal in the earth's crust, it is not commonly found in its pure form and is typically present in minerals. The production of titanium tetrachloride involves processing titanium concentrates with carbon and chlorine gas, followed by distillation for purification.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">四氯化钛，也称为氯化钛（IV）或TiCl4，是一种无色挥发性液体，在空气中水解并释放出白云。它用于克罗尔法将钛矿石转化为钛金属。尽管钛是地壳中含量第四丰富的金属，但它并不常见于纯金属，通常存在于矿物中。四氯化钛的生产包括用碳和氯气处理钛精矿，然后蒸馏提纯。</common:generalComment>
